    "production.text": '<p class="jstory">Production Line: Where Technology Meets Professional Expertise. We believe at our facility that fully automatic technology alone is not enough; it must be managed by expert minds monitoring every detail precisely. Therefore, our production line relies on a \"dual supervision\" system: complete machine automation and precise supervision by our specialized experts at every stage.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Pre-Press Stage —</b> Responsible: Pre-Press Specialist. This stage occurs digitally where the specialist ensures file accuracy, color separation, and measurement compliance before sending to plate production, eliminating any printing errors.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Paper Cutting —</b> Responsible: Cutting Specialist. Raw paper bobbins are transformed into fine sheets through automatic machines. The specialist adjusts measurement calibration with micrometric precision, ensuring sheets are perfectly ready for the next stage.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Offset Printing —</b> Responsible: Automatic Printing Specialist. Sheets move to offset machines at high speed. The printing expert monitors machine performance to maintain consistent pump speed and ensure uniform ink flow on every sheet.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Color Quality Inspection —</b> Responsible: Color Calibration Specialist. Here we use spectrum measurement devices, not just the naked eye. The specialist matches printed results with \"the standard sample,\" ensuring 100% color compliance.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Corrugated Board Production —</b> Responsible: Board Production Specialist. During this stage, the inner wavy layer is shaped. The specialist adjusts machine temperature and adhesive flow to ensure the cardboard achieves required strength and durability specifications.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Thermal Lamination —</b> Responsible: Lamination Specialist. Prints are coated with protective film. The lamination specialist monitors thermal adhesion and roller pressure, ensuring no bubbles or \"wrinkles\" appear and guaranteeing gloss or matte finish quality.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Mounting Stage —</b> Responsible: Mounting and Pattern Specialist. This is the most critical stage where printed paper is bonded with corrugated cardboard. The specialist ensures \"perfect registration\" between layers, preventing any misalignment affecting final box quality.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Cutting and Shaping —</b> Responsible: Cutting and Shaping Specialist. Specialized machines cut sheets and define fold lines. The specialist inspects blade precision and ensures cutting and shaping occur with meticulous accuracy.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Gluing and Folding —</b> Responsible: Finishing and Gluing Specialist. Boxes are folded and glued or stitched automatically. The specialist monitors adhesive distribution and fold integrity, ensuring boxes close tightly and fold easily for use.</p><p class="jstory"><b class="jhead">Counting, Packaging and Loading —</b> Responsible: Final Quality Assurance Specialist. At the final station, products are counted automatically. The specialist inspects random samples before final loading, ensuring products reach our customers in perfect condition. This integrated system guarantees that every piece leaving our printing facility is perfect, inspected by a specialist at each manufacturing step.</p>',
