    "catalog.kicker": "All Designs", "catalog.title": "Our packaging <span class=\"grad\">design</span> catalogue", "catalog.sub": "Every one of our 14 designs, explorable in 360&deg; 3D.", "catalog.back": "Home", "products.viewall": "View the catalogue",
    "box2.long": "The everyday workhorse of retail packaging. Printed on quality folding boxboard, die-cut, creased and delivered flat to save space, then set up in seconds. Ideal for cosmetics, food, pharma and general retail — with any finish you need: matte or gloss lamination, foil, or embossing.",
    "box3.long": "A straight-line carton bonded along a single side seam — the most common tuck-end box. Fast to produce and economical, it suits light to medium products where a clean, reliable closure matters. A perfect canvas for full-colour branding.",
    "box4.long": "A side-seam carton reinforced with two glue points for extra structural strength. The right choice for larger or heavier products that need a rigid body and a dependable seam that won't pop under load.",
    "box5.long": "An auto-lock base that snaps into shape the moment the box is opened — no taping, no manual assembly. It carries real weight, making it ideal for e-commerce, bottles, jars and heavier retail items that need a strong, fast-to-pack bottom.",
    "box6.long": "A tray-style carton glued at four corners to form a rigid open box. Popular for gift sets, produce, bakery and display trays where the contents are shown off and the structure must hold its shape.",
    "box7.long": "A deeper, sturdier tray built with six-corner gluing. It holds heavier contents and stacks well — a favourite for produce, hardware and industrial display packaging.",
    "box8.long": "A reinforced eight-corner box engineered for maximum rigidity and a premium, gift-grade presentation. Its double-wall corners resist crushing, making it a standout for luxury retail and heavier gift packaging.",
    "box9.long": "A carton that locks together with tabs and slots — no glue at all. Fully recyclable and easy to flat-pack and reuse, it is the sustainable choice for brands that want a clean, eco-conscious unboxing.",
    "box10.long": "Standard slotted corrugated containers (RSC) — the backbone of shipping and transit packaging. Strong, stackable and cost-effective, built to protect products through the supply chain, with print options for branded shippers.",
    "box11.long": "A two-piece box where a separate lid telescopes over the base — the classic rigid-box feel of premium electronics, apparel and gift packaging. Sturdy, reusable and unmistakably high-end, especially with foil, embossing or soft-touch finishes.",
    "box12.long": "Pop-up cartons that spring open from flat into a ready box in one motion — a huge time-saver on high-volume packing lines. They cut labour and speed up fulfilment without sacrificing a clean, branded look.",
    "box13.long": "Cartons fitted with a clear film window so shoppers can see the product without opening the box — a proven driver of shelf appeal and trust. Perfect for food, toys, cosmetics and gifts where the product sells itself.",
    "box14.long": "A finishing technique, not a shape: a selective high-gloss UV coating applied over a matte surface. The contrast makes logos and details catch the light and invites touch — an instant upgrade to premium perception at low cost.",
    "box15.long": "Metallic (or pigment) foil pressed onto the surface with a heated die — the timeless mark of luxury. Gold, silver, copper or holographic accents lift logos and typography, giving premium and gift packaging a genuinely crafted feel.",
    "clients.kicker": "Our Clients",
    "quality.note": "Quality here isn't a slogan — it's a system that starts with choosing food-contact materials and runs through colour management, printing, finishing and packing. We uphold international safety standards at every step, and all our inks and coatings are low-migration and food-contact safe — so your packaging reaches the consumer with full confidence and protects your brand's reputation.", "services.note": "We don't just fulfil the order as-is — we sit with each client to understand the real challenge: shipping cost, packaging strength, production speed, or how the product looks on the shelf, then propose the best solution both technically and commercially. Many clients have saved time and money thanks to a simple technical consultation before printing, turning a packaging problem into a competitive edge. Our expertise is with you from idea to delivery.", "clients.title": "Brands that <span class=\"grad\">trust</span> us", "clients.sub": "Brands around the world trust Mozaik.", "clients.note": "From startups to global brands, our clients choose Mozaik because they want a partner who understands that packaging is the first touch between their product and the customer. We work as an extension of their team — meeting deadlines, protecting quality, and keeping every design confidential. We don't measure our relationships by the number of orders, but by the trust that grows with each project — and that is what we are proudest of.",
